to the editor the benefits of repealing the estate tax far outweigh the concerns introduced by estate tax lawyers in questions raised on new bush plan to end estate tax front page jan 29 the possibility that some individuals may exploit loopholes is present in every change in the tax law that 's how these lawyers make their living however their concerns pale in comparison to the destructive nature of this tax on family businesses with rates ranging from 37 to 55 percent many families including newspaper owners have been forced to sell all or part of their businesses to pay the tax ending this tax would allow the orderly transfer of businesses from one generation to another unleash capital for the creation of new jobs stimulate long term investments encourage savings and promote local philanthropy john f sturm president newspaper association of america vienna va jan 30 2001

